rine]] was sunk in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] ({{coord|40|12|N|37|29|W}}) by two [[Grumman TBM Avenger]] aircraft based on {{USS|Card|CVE-11|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}) with the loss of seven of her 51 crew.<ref name=Card>{{cite DANFS |title=Card |url= http://www.hazegray.org/danfs/carriers/cve11.htm |accessdate=12 January 2012}}</ref><ref name=U664>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/boats/u664.htm |title=U-664 |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=15 April 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Italian destroyer|Vincenzo Gioberti||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Kingdom of Italy}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Oriani|destroyer}} was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] off [[La Spezia]] by {{HMS|Simoom|P225|6}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=seekrieg194308/> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==10 August==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=10 August 1943 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Asmara||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Kingdom of Italy|civil}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The cargo ship was [[torpedo]]ed and sunk in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] by {{HMS|Unshaken|P54|6}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=seekrieg194308/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Boy Federsen||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and damaged by Ilyushin Il-4 aircraft and sinks the next day.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soviet-empire.com/ussr/viewtopic.php?f=149&t=55255&sid=b64d81afc6dc3bf6ebf262ded5ddeaf9 |title=Soviet torpedo bomber victories during WWII |publisher=Sovietempire.com |accessdate=12 April 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Wakanoura Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[cargo liner]] was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Pacific Ocean]] north of [[Hokkaido]] by {{USS|Salmon|SS-182|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=Salmon>{{cite DANFS |title=Salmon |url= http://www.hazegray.org/danfs/submar/ss182.txt |accessdate=30 December 2011}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==11 August==\n{{shipwr