nean Sea]] off [[Bastia]], [[Corsica]], France by {{ship|Italian corvette|Euterpe||2}} and {{ship|Italian corvette|Minerva|1942|2}} (both {{navy|Kingdom of Italy}}) with the loss of four of her 50 crew. She was scuttled to prevent capture. The survivors were taken as [[prisoners of war]].<ref name=NH43/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|PiLB 316||2}}  \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The PiLB 40 type landing craft was lost on this date.<ref name=\"ReferenceD\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_pilb40.htm |title=PiBL 40 type landing craft, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=28 August 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|YC-970}} \n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=The non-self-propelled covered lighter was lost in [[Puget Sound, Washington]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.ibiblio.org/hyperwar/USN/USN-Chron/USN-Chron-1943.html |title=Official Chronology of the US Navy in WWII |publisher=Ibiblio |accessdate=14 August 2014}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==15 August==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=15 August 1943 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Cesco||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Kingdom of Italy|civil}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The [[tank ship|tanker]] was [[torpedo]]ed and sunk in the [[Adriatic Sea]] by {{HMS|Unruly|P49|6}} ({{navy|UK}}) east of [[Brindisi]], Italy.<ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=1137851|shipname=Cesco |accessdate=1 December 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|F 462||2}}  \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The Type C ''[[Marinefahrprahm]]'' was sunk on this date.<ref name=\"MFP landing craft, Germany\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_mfp.htm |title=MFP landing craft, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=28 August 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMS|LST-414}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[landing ship tank]] was sunk in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] off [