ayer|2}} was scuttled at Holmen Naval Base in Copenhagen to prevent capture by the Germans. Raised, repaired and returned to service May, 1945.<ref name=safari/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/denmark/dk_ms_lougen.htm |title=Mine warfare ships, Lougen, Minelayer (1941), Danish Royal Navy|publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=16 August 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship= {{HDMS|Lindormen|1940|6}} \n|flag={{navy|Denmark}}\n|desc=World War II: Operation Safari: The {{sclass-|Lindormen|minelayer|2}} was scuttled at Holmen Naval Base in Copenhagen to prevent capture by the Germans. raised, repaired and put in service as {{ship|German patrol ship|VS 1401||2}}  ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}).<ref name=safari/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/denmark/dk_ss_lindorman.htm |title=Mine warfare ships, lindormen  minelayer (1940), Danish Royal Navy |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=16 August 2017 }}{{Dead link|date=May 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HDMS|Lossen|1910|6}} \n|flag={{navy|Denmark}}\n|desc=World War II: Operation Safari: The minelayer was scuttled at Holmen Naval Base in Copenhagen to prevent capture by the Germans. Raised, repaired and put in Kriegsmarine service. Post-war transferred to the East German [[Volksmarine]] and served as the tugboat ''Wismar''.<ref name=safari/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/denmark/dk_ms_lossen.htm |title=Mine warfare ships, Lossen, Minelayer (1911), Danish Royal Navy|publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=15 August 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HDMS|Lougen|1941|6}} \n|flag={{navy|Denmark}}\n|desc=[[File:Lougen sunken on 29 August 1943.jpg|thumb|''Lougen'']]\nWorld War II: Operation Safari: The {{sclass-|Lougen|minelayer|2}} was scuttled at Holmen Naval Base in Copenhagen to prevent capture by the Germans. Raised, repaired and returned to service May, 1945.<ref name=safari/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.na