www.hazegray.org/danfs/submar/ss266.txt |accessdate= 4 January 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Normandiet||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Denmark}}\n|desc=The cargo ship collided with {{SS|Maasburg||2}} ({{flag|Netherlands}}) in the [[Elbe]], She broke in two and sank. The wreck was dispersed in 1948.<ref name=Jordan446>{{cite book |title=The world's merchant fleets, 1939 |first=Roger |last=Jordan |publisher=Chatham publishing |location=London |year=1999 |page=446 |isbn=1 86176 023 X}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|PT-117}} \n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[Electric Launch Company|Elco]] 80' [[PT boat]] was beached and abandoned after being bombed by Japanese dive bombers in [[Rendova Island|Rendova Harbour]] ({{coord|08|24|S|157|19|E}}).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/10161.html |title=PT-117 of the US Navy |publisher=U Boat.net |accessdate=1 August 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|PT-164}} \n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[Electric Launch Company|Elco]] 80' [[PT boat]] was bombed and sunk by Japanese horizontal bombers in Rendova Harbor, [[Soloman Islands]] ({{coord|08|25|S|157|20|E}}).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/10208.html |title=PT-164 of the US Navy |publisher=U Boat.net |accessdate=1 August 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Soviet submarine|S-12||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[Soviet S-class submarine|S-class]] [[submarine]] struck a [[naval mine|mine]] and sank in the [[Baltic Sea]] north of Naissaay Island.<ref name=seekrieg194308/><ref>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/5097.html |title=S-12 of the Soviet Navy |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=1 August 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-383||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC submarine]] was [[depth charge]]d and sunk 