: The boat struck a mine and sank in the [[Kara Sea]] ({{Coord|68|40|N|51|51|E}}).<ref name=Majakovski>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/3037.html |title=Majakovski |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=9 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Italian torpedo boat|Pallade|1937|2}} \n|flag={{navy|Kingdom of Italy}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|Spica|torpedo boat}} capsized and sank during an American air raid on Naples.<ref name=seekrieg194308/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|Plymouth|PG-57|6}} \n|flag={{navy|USA}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[gunboat]] was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] {{convert|90|nmi|km}} east of [[Elizabeth City, New Jersey]] ({{coord|36|17|N|74|29|W}}) by {{GS|U-566||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of 70 of her 155 crew. Survivors were rescued by {{USCGC|Calypso|WPG-104|6}} ({{navy|USA|coast guard}}).<ref name=Plymouth>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/3035.html |title=USS Plymouth (PG 57) |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=9 April 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMT|Red Gauntlet}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[naval trawler]] was torpedoed and sunk in the [[North Sea]] off [[Harwich]], [[Essex]] by {{ship|German torpedo boat|S-86||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of all 21 crew.<ref name=NH43>{{cite web |url=http://www.naval-history.net/xDKWW2-4300-49ALL.htm |title=Naval Events, January-December 1943 (in outline only) |publisher=Naval History |accessdate=29 December 2011}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Shoju Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the [[East China Sea]] off the coast of [[Formosa]] by {{USS|Pike|SS-173|6}} ({{navy|USA}}).<ref name=seekrieg194307/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-34|1936|2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIA submarine]] collided with {{ship|German tender|Lech||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) at [[Klaip\u00e9da|Memel]], Lithuania and sank with the loss of four of her 43 crew. She was raised on 24 August and later scrapped. }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==6 August==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=6 August 1943 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship= {{ship|Japanese destroyer|Arashi||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: [[Battle of Vella Gulf]]: The {{sclass-|Kager\u014d|destroyer}} was [[torpedo]]ed and sunk in [[Vella Gulf]] between [[Kolombangara]] and [[Vella Lavella]] ({{coord|07|50|S|156|55|E}}) by the destroyers {{USS|Craven|DD-382|6}}, {{USS|Dunlap|DD-384|6}} and {{USS|Maury|DD-401|6}} (all {{navy|USA|1912}}).\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Fort Halkett||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[Fort ship]] was torpedoed, shelled and sunk in the [[South Atlantic]] {{convert|600|nmi|km}} south east of [[Natal, Brazil]] ({{coord|9|30|S|25|50|W}}) by {{GS|U-185||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}). All 59 crew survived; they were rescued by the destroyer {{USS|Goldsborough|DD-188|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}) or reached land in their [[lifeboat (shipboard)|lifeboats]].<ref name=FortAJ>{{cite web |url=http://www.mariners-l.co.uk/FortA.html |title=Fort Ships A-J |publisher=Mariners |accessdate=5 January 2012}}</ref><ref name=FH>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/3038.html |title=Fort Halkett |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=8 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Italian patrol boat|Brindisi||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Kingdom of Italy}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[patrol boat]] was torpedoed and sunk in the Mediterranean Sea by the [[submarine]] {{HMS|Uproar|P31|6}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=seekrieg194308/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship= {{ship|Japanese destroyer|Hagikaze||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Battle of Vella Gulf]]: The {{sclass-|Kager\u014d|destroyer|2}} was torpedoed and sunk in Vella Gulf 