lmon>{{cite DANFS |title=Salmon |url= http://www.hazegray.org/danfs/submar/ss182.txt |accessdate=30 December 2011}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==11 August==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=11 August 1943 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ss|Jutoku Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk by a [[Consolidated B-24 Liberator]] aircraft in the [[Pacific Ocean]] north east of [[Lorengau]], [[Manus Island]] ({{coord|01|11|S|148|08|E}}).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.combinedfleet.com/W-22_t.htm |title=Japanese Minesweepers |publisher=Combinedfleet.com |accessdate=11 August 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Soviet motor torpedo boat|No. 95||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[G-5-class motor torpedo boat]] was sunk in the Black Sea by German motor torpedo boats.<ref name=\"G-5 class motor torpedo boat, USSR\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/russia/ru_cf_g5.htm |title=G-5 class motor torpedo boat, USSR |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=19 September 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"soviet Empire\">{{cite web |url=http://www.soviet-empire.com/ussr/viewtopic.php?f=149&t=53917 |title=Soviet Naval Battles-Black Sea during WWII(redone)|publisher=soviet Empire |accessdate=10 August 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|PiLB 101||2}}  \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The PiLB 39 Type personnel landing craft was lost on this date.<ref name=\"navypedia.org\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_pilb39.htm |title=PiLB 39 Type personnel landing craft, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=28 August 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German motor torpedo boat|S 121||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[E-boat|Type 1939/40]] [[motor torpedo boat]] was sunk in the [[English Channel]] in a British air attack.<ref name=seekrieg194308/><ref>[http://