ubmarine Accidents & Disasters |first=Edwyn |last=Gray |publisher=Pen and Sword |year=2006 |page=179 |isbn=0-85052-987-5}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==13 August==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=13 August 1943 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Argus|1940|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The cargo ship was sunk by the explosion of her cargo of ammunition at [[Hamnbukt]], [[Porsanger]], Norway.<ref name=NH034212>{{cite web |url=http://www.naval-history.net/xDKWW2-4203-43MAR01.htm |title=Naval Events, March 1942, Part 1 of 2, Sunday 1st - Saturday 14th |publisher=Naval History |accessdate=28 December 2011}}</ref><ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=5614059|shipname=Argus |accessdate=1 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Edo Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The cargo ship was [[torpedo]]ed and sunk in the [[South China Sea]] off [[Formosa]] by {{USS|Sunfish|SS-281|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=Sunfish>{{cite DANFS |title=Sunfish |url= http://www.hazegray.org/danfs/submar/ss281.htm |accessdate=4 January 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Francis W. Pettygrove||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United States|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[Liberty ship]] was torpedoed and damaged in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] ({{coord|36|08|N|2|14|W}}) by [[Luftwaffe]] aircraft. She was towed to [[Gibraltar]] and beached but was declared a [[constructive total loss]].<ref name=LibF>{{cite web |url=http://www.mariners-l.co.uk/LibShipsF.html |title=Liberty Ships - F |publisher=Mariners |accessdate=6 January 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|John Penn|APA-23|6}} \n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|John Penn|attack transport}} was torpedoed and sunk off [[Guadalcanal]] by Japanese aircraft.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wrecksite.eu/wreck.aspx?107884 |title=John Penn Cargo Ship 1931-1943|publisher=Wrecksite |accessdate=13 August 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwr