ay, and sank.<ref>{{cite book|last=Hegland |first=Jon Rustung |title=Angrep i skj\u00e6rg\u00e5rden &ndash; Norske motortorpedob\u00e5ters operasjoner fra Shetland 1941&ndash;1945 |publisher=Dreyers Forlag A/S |location=Oslo |year=1989 |page=97 |isbn=82-09-105337 |language=Norwegian}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==14 August==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=14 August 1943 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German siebel ferry|Fulda|SF 31|2}}    \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The [[Siebel ferry]] was lost on this date.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_sf40.htm |title=Siebelfahre 40 and Siebelfahre 41, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=28 August 2016}}</ref> \n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|M. H. de Young||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United States|1912}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The [[Liberty ship]] was [[torpedo]]ed and damaged in the [[Pacific Ocean]] ({{coord|21|50|S|175|10|E}}) by {{Jsub|I-19||2}} ({{navy|Empire of Japan}}). She consequently became the [[hulk (ship)|hulk]] USS ''Antelope''.<ref name=LibM>{{cite web |url=http://www.mariners-l.co.uk/LibShipsM.html |title=Liberty Ships - M |publisher=Mariners |accessdate=6 January 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German siebel ferry|SF 148||2}}    \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The [[Siebel ferry]] was sunk on this date.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_sf40.htm |title=Siebelfahre 40 and Siebelfahre 41, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=28 August 2016}}</ref> \n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German siebel ferry|SF 242||2}}    \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The [[Siebel ferry]] was sunk on this date.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_sf40.htm |title=Siebelfahre 40 and Siebelfahre 41, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=28 August 2016}}</ref> \n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=