ean off Vella Lavella by {{USS|Chevalier|DD-451|6}}, {{USS|Nicholas|DD-449|6}}, {{USS|O'Bannon|DD-450|6}} and {{USS|Taylor|DD-468|6}} (all {{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=seekrieg194308/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|J. Pinckney Henderson||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United States|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Convoy HX 252]]: The [[Liberty ship]] collided in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] with {{MV|J. H. Senior||2}} ({{flag|Panama}}) and caught fire. ''J. Pinckney Henderson'' was towed to [[Sydney, Nova Scotia]], Canada where she was beached. The ship, which was on her [[maiden voyage]] was a total loss. ''J. H. Senior'' was towed to [[Bay Bulls, Newfoundland and Labrador|Bay Bulls]], [[Dominion of Newfoundland|Newfoundland]] where she was also declared a total loss. There were three survivors from ''J. Pinckney Henderson'' and six from ''J. H. Senior''.<ref name=LibJ>{{cite web |url=http://www.mariners-l.co.uk/LibShipsJ-Ji.html |title=Liberty Ships J - Ji |publisher=Mariners |accessdate=6 January 2012}}</ref><ref name=HX252W>{{cite web |url=http://www.warsailors.com/convoys/hx252page4.html |title=Report from The Flag Officer Newfoundland (ST. John's) |publisher=Warsailors |accessdate=18 May 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMS|LCT 301}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|LCT 3|landing craft tank}} was lost when {{HMS|LCT 416}} ({{navy|UK}}) exploded and sank at [[Tripoli]], [[Italian Libya|Libya]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/17809.html |title=HMS LCT 301 of the Royal Navy |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=18 August 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMS|LCT 416}} \n|flag={{navy|UK}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass-|LCT 3|landing craft tank}} exploded and sank at Tripoli, Libya.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/17249.html |title=HMS LCT 416 of the Royal Navy |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=18 August 2013 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|LST-396}} \n|flag={{nav