|nmi|km}} north north east of [[Beirut]], [[French Lebanon|Lebanon]] by {{GS|U-596||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of nine of her 11 crew.<ref name=Lily>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/3047.html |title=Lily |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=11 April 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Namaz'' \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The sailing ship was shelled and sunk in the Mediterranean Sea ({{coord|33|42|N|34|43|E}}) by {{GS|U-596||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}). All crew survived.<ref name=Namaz>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/3046.html |title=Namaz |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=11 April 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Panikos'' \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The sailing ship was shelled and sunk in the Mediterranean Sea ({{coord|33|42|N|34|43|E}}) by {{GS|U-596||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}). All crew survived.<ref name=Panikos>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/3045.html |title=Panikos |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=11 April 2012}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==22 August==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=22 August 1943 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''DB-36'' and ''DB-37''\n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The No. 1-class landing boats were shelled and sunk, or captured and scuttled with explosives, in the [[Black Sea]] by {{GS|U-24|1936|2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}). All six crew were taken as [[prisoners of war]].<ref name=DB36>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/3049.html |title=DB-36 |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=4 February 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/russia/ru_ls_db.htm |title=No. 1 class landing boat, USSR |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=21 September 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"ReferenceF\">{{cite web |url=http://www.soviet-empire.com/ussr/viewtopic.php?f=149&t=53917 |title=Soviet Naval Battles-Black Sea during WWII(redone)|pu