}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of fifteen of her 38 crew. Survivors were rescued by {{ship|Soviet minesweeper|SKA-0108||2}} ({{navy|Soviet Union}}).<ref name=seekrieg194308/><ref name=Dzhalita>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/3059.html |title=TSC-11 Dzhalita |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=3 February 2012}}</ref> \n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HDMS|Triton|1915|6}} \n|flag={{navy|Denmark}}\n|desc=World War II: Operation Safari: The {{sclass-|\u00c6ger|submarine|2}} was scuttled at Holmen Naval Base in Copenhagen to prevent capture by the Germans.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/denmark/dk_ss_aegir.htm |title=\u00c6ger Submarines (1915-1917), Danish Royal Navy|publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=16 August 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==30 August==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=30 August 1943 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{Ship|Soviet gunboat|BK-122||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The Type 1124 gunboat was shelled and sunk in the [[Bay of Taganrod]] by {{ship|German gunboat|MAL-1||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}).<ref name=\"Red Fleet,Black Sea\">{{cite web |url=http://www.soviet-empire.com/ussr/viewtopic.php?f=149&t=53917&sid=cf2e067f65c3cd13e8ea4c14698c3173 |title=Red Fleet,Black Sea |publisher=soviet Empire |accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{Ship|Soviet gunboat|BK-312||2}}\n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=World War II: The Type 1125 gunboat was shelled and sunk in the Bay of Taganrod by {{ship|German gunboat|MAL-1||2}}  ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}).<ref name=\"Red Fleet,Black Sea\">{{cite web |url=http://www.soviet-empire.com/ussr/viewtopic.php?f=149&t=53917&sid=cf2e067f65c3cd13e8ea4c14698c3173 |title=Red Fleet,Black Sea |publisher=soviet Empire |accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Soviet minesweeper|No-605||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass2-|KM|minesweeper}} was 