t submarine|Shch-130||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=The {{sclass-|Shchuka|submarine}} collided with {{ship|Soviet submarine|Shch-128||2}} ({{navy|Soviet Union}}) and sank in [[Golden Horn Bay]] off [[Vladivostok]]. She was raised on 3 September, repaired and returned to service.<ref name=seekrieg194308/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Shoto Maru||2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the Luzon Strait by {{USS|Seawolf|SS-197|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=seekrieg194308/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|W. S. Rheem||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United States|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: The tanker was torpedoed and damaged in the [[Pacific Ocean]] off the [[New Hebrides]] by {{Jsub|I-182||2}} ({{navy|Empire of Japan}}). She was scuttled on 8 September by {{USS|Wadsworth|DD-516|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=seekrieg194308/> \n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==Unknown date==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=Unknown date 1943 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|F 336||2}}  \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The Type C ''[[Marinefahrprahm]]'' was sunk sometime in August.<ref name=\"MFP landing craft, Germany\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_mfp.htm |title=MFP landing craft, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=28 August 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|I-O-23||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=The ''Siebelgef\u00e4\u00df'' landing craft was sunk sometime in August.<ref name=\"ReferenceB\">{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_siebelgefass.htm |title=SiebelgefaB type personnel landing craft, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=28 August 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|I-O-79||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc= The ''Siebelgef\u00e4\u00df'' landing craft was sunk sometime in August.<ref name=\