.svg}} || 1871\u20131901 || [[Augusta of Saxe-Weimar|Empress Augusta]] and<br>[[Victoria, Princess Royal|Empress Frederick]]'s Standard || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Kaiserinstandarte 1888.svg}} || 1888\u20131918 || Empress [[Augusta Viktoria of Schleswig-Holstein|Augusta Viktoria]]'s Standard || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Kronprinzenstandarte Version1.svg}} || 1871\u20131888 || Standard of the [[Crown Prince]] ||\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Kronprinzenstandarte Version2.svg}} || 1888\u20131918 || Standard of the Crown Prince \n|| \n|}\n\n=== Weimar Republic (1919\u20131933) ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:110px\"|Flag !! style=\"width:100px\"|Date !! style=\"width:250px\"|Use !! style=\"width:250px\"|Description\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flag of Germany (3-2 aspect ratio).svg}} || 1919\u20131933 || National flag ({{lang|de|Nationalflagge}}) ||\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flagge Deutsches Reich - Dienstflagge zu Land (1921-1933).svg}} || 1921\u20131933 || State flag ({{lang|de|Dienstflagge zu Land}}) ||\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Merchant flag of Germany (1919\u20131933).svg}} || 1919\u20131933 || Merchant flag ({{lang|de|Handelsflagge}}) ||\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flag of Weimar Republic (merchant+cross).svg}} || 1921\u20131933 || Merchant flag variant with the Iron Cross ({{lang|de|Eisernes Kreuz}}) ||\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flagge Deutsches Reich - Dienstflagge zur See (1921-1926).svg}} || 1921\u20131926 || State ensign ({{lang|de|Dienstflagge zur See}}) ||\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Seedienstflagge 1926-1933.svg}} || 1926\u20131933 || State ensign ({{lang|de|Dienstflagge zur See}}) ||\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|War Ensign of Germany (Proposed 1919).svg}} || 1919\u20131921 (de jure) || Reich war flag ({{lang|de|Reichskriegsflagge}}) ||\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flag of Weimar Republic (war).svg}} || 1921\u20131933 || Reich war flag || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flag of Weimar Republic (jack).svg}} || 1921\u20131933 || Marine jack ({{lang|de|Kriegsg\u00f6sch}}) || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flag of the President of Germany.svg}} || 1921\u20131926 || Standard of the President || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flag of the President of Germany (1926\u20131933).svg}} || 1926\u20131933 || Standard of the President || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flag of the President of Germany (1919\u20131921).svg}} || 1919\u20131921 || Flag of the President || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flag of Weimar Republic (defence minister 1919).svg}} || 1919\u20131921 || Flag of Defence Minister || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flag of Weimar Republic (defence minister 1921).svg}} || 1921\u20131933 || Flag of Defence Minister || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flagge Reichsbanner 2013.jpg}} || 1924\u20131933;<br>since 1953 || Flag of the ''[[Reichsbanner Schwarz-Rot-Gold]]'' || The {{lang|de|Reichsbanner Schwarz-Rot-Gold}} was an unofficial republican paramilitary organization dominated by social democrats, liberals, and members of the Catholic Centre Party, to defend the Weimar Republic against [[National Socialists]], communists, and monarchists. Refounded in 1953 as an association for political education.\n|}\n\n==={{anchor|National Socialist Germany|Third Reich}} Nazi Germany (1933\u20131945) ===\n{{See also|Flag of Germany#Nazi Germany and World War II (1933\u20131945)|Blutfahne}}\n\nThe flag with the ''Hakenkreuz'' and white disc centered was used throughout (1920\u201345) as the [[NSDAP]] party flag ({{lang|de|Parteiflagge}}).<ref name=\"Herzfeld\"/> Between 1933 and 1935, it was used as the national flag ({{lang|de|Nationalflagge}}) and merchant flag ({{lang|de|Handelsflagge}}) - interchangeably with the black-white-red horizontal tricolour last used (up to 1918) by the [[German Empire]]. In 1935, the black-white-red horizontal tricolour was scrapped again, and the flag with the ''off-center'' ''Hakenkreuz'' and disc was instituted as the only national flag (and was to remain as such until 1945). The flag with the centered disc only continued to be used as the ''Parteiflagge'' after 1935.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:110px\"|Flag !! style=\"width:100px\"|Date !! style=\"width:250px\"|Use !! style=\"width:250px\"|Description\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\" | Flags used 1933\u20131935\n|- \n| {{ListFlag|Flag of the NSDAP (1920\u20131945).svg}}\n| {{plainlist|\n*1933\u20131935\n*1933\u20131935\n*1920\u20131945}}\n| {{plainlist|\n*National flag ({{lang|de|Nationalflagge}})\n*Merchant flag ({{lang|de|Handelsflagge}})\n*[[Nazi Party]] flag ({{lang|de|Parteiflagge}})<ref name=\"Herzfeld\"/>}}\n| A red field, with a white disc with a black [[swastika]], or {{lang|de|hakenkreuz}}, at a 45 degree angle. Disc and swastika are exactly in the centre.\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|National flag of Germany 1933-1935.svg}}\n| 1933\u20131935\n| {{plainlist|\n*National flag ({{lang|de|Nationalflagge}})\n*Merchant flag ({{lang|de|Handelsflagge}})}}\n| Black, white, and red horizontal tricolour. Used in conjunction with the ''Parteiflagge''.\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Handelsflagge mit dem EK 1933-1935.svg}} || 1933\u20131935 || Merchant flag variant with the Iron Cross ({{lang|de|Eisernes Kreuz}}) || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|War Ensign of Germany 1933-1935.svg}} || 1933\u20131935 || Reich war flag ({{lang|de|Reichskriegsflagge}}) and marine jack || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Dienstflagge Wehrmachtbeh\u00f6rden zur See 1933.svg}} || 1933 || Reich service flag ({{lang|de|Reichsdienstflagge}}) of the {{lang|de|[[Wehrmacht]]}} || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Reichsdienstflagge 1933-1935.svg}} || 1933\u20131935 || Reich service flag || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Standarte Reichspr\u00e4sident 1933-1935.svg}} || 1933\u20131935 (de facto up to 1934) || Standard of the President || \n|- \n| {{ListFlag|RKM 1933 - 1935.svg|border=}} || 1933\u20131935 || Flag of the Minister of Defence || \n|-\n! colspan=\"4\" | Flags used 1935\u20131945\n|- \n| {{ListFlag|Flag of Germany (1935\u20131945).svg}}\n| {{plainlist|\n*1935\u20131945\n*1935\u20131945}}\n| {{plainlist|\n*National flag<ref name=\"Herzfeld\"/>\n*Marine jack&nbsp;({{lang|de|G\u00f6sch}})}}\n| A red field, with a white disc with a black [[swastika]], or {{lang|de|hake