 [[Flag of Germany#History|Standard]] ||\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Kaiserstandarte Version2.svg}} || 1871\u20131888 || [[German Emperor]]'s Standard || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Kaiserstandarte.svg}} || 1888\u20131918 || German Emperor's Standard || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Kaiserinnenstandarte 1871.svg}} || 1871\u20131901 || [[Augusta of Saxe-Weimar|Empress Augusta]] and<br>[[Victoria, Princess Royal|Empress Frederick]]'s Standard || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Kaiserinstandarte 1888.svg}} || 1888\u20131918 || Empress [[Augusta Viktoria of Schleswig-Holstein|Augusta Viktoria]]'s Standard || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Kronprinzenstandarte Version1.svg}} || 1871\u20131888 || Standard of the [[Crown Prince]] ||\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Kronprinzenstandarte Version2.svg}} || 1888\u20131918 || Standard of the Crown Prince \n|| \n|}\n\n=== Weimar Republic (1919\u20131933) ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:110px\"|Flag !! style=\"width:100px\"|Date !! style=\"width:250px\"|Use !! style=\"width:250px\"|Description\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flag of Germany (3-2 aspect ratio).svg}} || 1919\u20131933 || National flag ({{lang|de|Nationalflagge}}) ||\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flagge Deutsches Reich - Dienstflagge zu Land (1921-1933).svg}} || 1921\u20131933 || State flag ({{lang|de|Dienstflagge zu Land}}) ||\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Merchant flag of Germany (1919\u20131933).svg}} || 1919\u20131933 || Merchant flag ({{lang|de|Handelsflagge}}) ||\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flag of Weimar Republic (merchant+cross).svg}} || 1921\u20131933 || Merchant flag variant with the Iron Cross ({{lang|de|Eisernes Kreuz}}) ||\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flagge Deutsches Reich - Dienstflagge zur See (1921-1926).svg}} || 1921\u20131926 || State ensign ({{lang|de|Dienstflagge zur See}}) ||\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Seedienstflagge 1926-1933.svg}} || 1926\u20131933 || State ensign ({{lang|de|Dienstflagge zur See}}) ||\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|War Ensign of Germany (Proposed 1919).svg}} || 1919\u20131921 (de jure) || Reich war flag ({{lang|de|Reichskriegsflagge}}) ||\n|-\n| {{ListFlag