isc was instituted as the only national flag (and was to remain as such until 1945). The flag with the centered disc only continued to be used as the ''Parteiflagge'' after 1935.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:110px\"|Flag !! style=\"width:100px\"|Date !! style=\"width:250px\"|Use !! style=\"width:250px\"|Description\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\" | Flags used 1933\u20131935\n|- \n| {{ListFlag|Flag of the NSDAP (1920\u20131945).svg}}\n| {{plainlist|\n*1933\u20131935\n*1933\u20131935\n*1920\u20131945}}\n| {{plainlist|\n*National flag ({{lang|de|Nationalflagge}})\n*Merchant flag ({{lang|de|Handelsflagge}})\n*[[Nazi Party]] flag ({{lang|de|Parteiflagge}})<ref name=\"Herzfeld\"/>}}\n| A red field, with a white disc with a black [[swastika]], or {{lang|de|hakenkreuz}}, at a 45 degree angle. Disc and swastika are exactly in the centre.\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|National flag of Germany 1933-1935.svg}}\n| 1933\u20131935\n| {{plainlist|\n*National flag ({{lang|de|Nationalflagge}})\n*Merchant flag ({{lang|de|Handelsflagge}})}}\n| Black, white, and red horizontal tricolour. Used in conjunction with the ''Parteiflagge''.\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Handelsflagge mit dem EK 1933-1935.svg}} || 1933\u20131935 || Merchant flag variant with the Iron Cross ({{lang|de|Eisernes Kreuz}}) || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|War Ensign of Germany 1933-1935.svg}} || 1933\u20131935 || Reich war flag ({{lang|de|Reichskriegsflagge}}) and marine jack || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Dienstflagge Wehrmachtbeh\u00f6rden zur See 1933.svg}} || 1933 || Reich service flag ({{lang|de|Reichsdienstflagge}}) of the {{lang|de|[[Wehrmacht]]}} || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Reichsdienstflagge 1933-1935.svg}} || 1933\u20131935 || Reich service flag || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Standarte Reichspr\u00e4sident 1933-1935.svg}} || 1933\u20131935 (de facto up to 1934) || Standard of the President || \n|- \n| {{ListFlag|RKM 1933 - 1935.svg|border=}} || 1933\u20131935 || Flag of the Minister of Defence || \n|-\n! colspan=\"4\" | Flags used 1935\u20131945\n|- \n| {{ListFlag|Flag of Germany (1935\u20131945).svg}}\n| {{plainlist|\n*1935\u20131945\n*1935\u20131945}}\n| {{plainlist|\n*National flag<ref name=\"Herzfeld\"/>\n*Marine jack&nbsp;({{lang|de|G\u00f6sch}})}}\n| A red field, with a white disc with a black [[swastika]], or {{lang|de|hakenkreuz}}, at a 45 degree angle. Disk and swastika are slightly off-centre.\n|- \n| {{ListFlag|Flag of the NSDAP (1920\u20131945).svg}} || 1920\u20131945 || [[Nazi Party]] flag ({{lang|de|Parteiflagge}})<ref name=\"Herzfeld\"/> || A red field, with a white disc with a black [[swastika]], or {{lang|de|hakenkreuz}}, at a 45 degree angle. Disk and swastika are exactly in the centre.\n|-\n| [[File:Banner of Germany 1933.svg|50px]] || 1933\u20131945 || Banner ({{lang|de|Bannerflagge}}) of Germany || Banners were of various lengths, which were hung vertically on public buildings.\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Handelsflagge mit dem Eisernen Kreuz 1935.svg}} || 1935\u20131945 || Merchant flag variant with the Iron Cross || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|War Ensign of Germany 1935-1938.svg}} || 1935\u20131938 || ''Kriegsmarine'', ''Heer'', ''Luftwaffe'' \n|- \n| {{ListFlag|War Ensign of Germany 1938-1945.svg}} || 1938\u20131945 || ''Kriegsmarine'', ''Heer'', ''Luftwaffe''\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Reichsdienstflagge 1935.svg}} || 1935\u20131945 || Reich service flag || \n|- \n| {{ListFlag|Standarte Adolf Hitlers.svg}} || 1935\u20131945 || [[Adolf Hitler's personal standard|Standard of Adolf Hitler]] || \n|- \n| {{ListFlag|Wehrmacht_Commander-in-Chief_flag.svg}} || 1935\u20131938 || Flag of the {{lang|de|Wehrmacht}} Commander in Chief (replaced the Minister of Defence) || \n|- \n| {{ListFlag|Flag Schutzstaffel.svg}} || 1935\u20131945 || Flag of the {{lang|de|[[Schutzstaffel]]}} (SS) || \n|- \n| {{ListFlag|Ordnungspolizei flag.svg}} || 1936\u20131945 || Flag of the {{lang|de|[[Ordnungspolizei]] (OrPo)}} (\"Order Police\", the national regular police organization of Nazi Germany) || \n|- \n| {{ListFlag|Hitlerjugend Allgemeine Flagge.svg}} || 1933\u20131945 || Flag of the [[Hitler Youth]], a youth organization in the Nazi Party ||\n|-\n|}\n\n=== World War II aftermath in Germany ===\n[[Allied Control Council]] (1945\u20131949) and [[Saar Protectorate]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:110px\"|Flag !! style=\"width:100px\"|Date !! style=\"width:250px\"|Use !! style=\"width:250px\"|Description\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flag of Germany (1946-1949).svg|border=}} || 1946\u20131950 || \"C-Pennant\" ({{lang|de|C-Doppelstander}}) (provisional [[civil ensign]]) || Used during the [[Allied-occupied Germany|Occupation Period]] to identify German ships according to international law.\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flag of Saar (1947%E2%80%931956).svg|border=}} || 1947\u20131957 || Flag of [[Saar Protectorate]] || Flag of Saarland which was given by French Government. at this time period Saar was satellite state of France.\n|}\n\n==={{anchor|DDR\u2014[[East Germany]] (1949\u20131990)}} East Germany (1949\u20131990)===\n{{see also|Flag of East Germany}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:110px\"|Flag !! style=\"width:100px\"|Date !! style=\"width:250px\"|Use !! style=\"width:250px\"|Description\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flag of Germany.svg}} || 1949\u20131959 || State flag ({{lang|de|Staatsflagge}}) || \n|- \n| {{ListFlag|Flag of German Democratic Republic.svg}} || 1959\u20131990 || State flag ({{lang|de|Staatsflagge}}) 1959\u20131990<br />Merchant flag ({{lang|de|Handelsflagge}}) 1973\u20131990 || Tricolour of black, red, and yellow (same as West German colours), but bears the coat of arms of East Germany, consisting of a [[Compass (drawing tool)|compass]] and a hammer encircled with rye\n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flag of East Germany - merchant 1959-1973.svg}} || 1959\u20131973 || Merchant flag ({{lang|de|Handelsflagge}}) || \n|-\n| [[File:Flag of East Germany (Hanging).svg|50px]] || 1963\u20131990 || Hanging state flag ({{lang|de|Bannerflagge}}) || \n|-\n| {{ListFlag|Flag of German post (East Germany).svg}} || 1955\u20131973